Lawyer Christian Schertz said the player would seek compensation for "moral harm commensurate with the seriousness of the breach, which is probably one of the most serious violations of privacy in recent years".
The alleged incident is said to have occurred in June 2009 in a suite of the Palms Hotel and Casino in Las Vegas.
After meeting at a nightclub, Ronaldo and Majorca returned to the player's room, where he allegedly raped her, according to documents filed in Clark County District Court in Nevada.
Majorca claims that Ronaldo fell to his knees after the alleged incident and told her he was "99 percent" a "good guy", but was betrayed by the other "one percent".
The documents say that Ronaldo admits they had sexual intercourse, but that it was consensual.
Majorca also claims that she went to the police and a hospital where her injuries were photographed, but later agreed to an out-of-court settlement because she was "afraid of reprisals" and worried about her "public humiliation".
The 34-year-old says she's trying to reverse the settlement as she continues to suffer from post-traumatic stress disorder from the alleged incident.
