Christian Abercrombie undergoing emergency surgery after a head injury.
Tennessee State Tigers quarterback Christian Abercrombie underwent emergency surgery after suffering a head injury in Saturday's game, where the Tigers were defeated 31-27 by the Vanderbilt Commodores, Tennessean newspaper reporter Mike Organ reported.
Tennessee State head coach Rod Reed told reporters that the injury occurred just before halftime.
