But playing can be difficult.
You must endure a lot on a weekly basis.
I'm still struggling with the stress and pressure of work, but the coaching job is a perfect fit.
I've always wanted to coach, and now that I'm doing it, I feel more comfortable with myself than I have in my entire adult life".
You can hear the full interview on Sportsound on Sunday 30 September, on Radio Scotland between 12:00 and 13:00 BST.
The best time to drink beer is 5:30 on a Saturday, according to a study.
The summer heat has boosted profits for Britain's experimental pubs but put more pressure on restaurant chains.
Pubs and bars saw sales increase 2.7 percent in July, but restaurant profits fell 4.8 percent, the figures revealed.
Peter Martin, of the business consultancy CGA, which compiled the data, said: "The continuing sunshine and England's longer than expected World Cup attendance resulted in July following a similar pattern to the previous month, June, when pubs' profits rose 2.8 percent, but restaurants took an even bigger hit.
The 1.8 percent decline in restaurant revenue in June only worsened in July.
Pubs and bars serving alcohol fared better, with previous years' figures rising more than their restaurant counterparts fell.
Pubs serving food also suffered on sunny days, though not as dramatically as restaurants.
Looks like people just want to go out for a drink.
In all the pubs and bars operated, sales of drinks increased by 6.6 percent for the month, while food sales decreased by three percent".
Paul Newman, from the leisure and hospitality analysts division at RSM, said: "These results confirm the trend we have seen since the end of April.
