A patch of Red Tide stretches for about 130 miles of coastline from Pinellas County in the north to Lee County in the south.
Spots are being spotted about 10 miles off the coast of Hillsborough County, but in fewer spots than last week.
Red tide has also been observed in Pasco County.
Moderate concentrations were recorded in coastal and offshore Pinellas County last week, low to high concentrations were recorded offshore Hillsborough County, background concentrations to high concentrations in Manatee County, background concentrations to high concentrations on or off the coast in Sarasota County, background concentrations to moderate concentrations in Charlotte County, background concentrations to high concentrations on or off the coast in Lehigh County, and low concentrations in Lehigh County.
Respiratory disturbances continue to be reported in Pinellas, Manatee, Sarasota, Lee and Collier counties.
No respiratory disturbances have been reported in northwest Florida in the past week.
